The paper discusses a framework for programming and deploying neuromorphic systems, which involves spiking neural dynamics and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions machine learning and brain-inspired neural algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the energy benefits of neuromorphic computing, which could place it in cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) or cs.AR (Architecture).
